    category: 'planning',
    helpText: 'Life transitions can significantly disrupt chronic illness management routines and access to care, making advance planning essential for maintaining stability. Document how to transfer medical records, research healthcare providers in new locations, and maintain medication access during transitions. Include strategies for managing stress-related symptom flares that often accompany major changes, and create backup plans for accessing care if your usual support systems are temporarily unavailable.'
