<parameter name="old_string">    helpText: 'A functional capacity evaluation provides objective documentation of your physical and cognitive abilities, which is crucial for workplace accommodations, disability claims, and treatment planning. This assessment measures your ability to perform specific tasks like lifting, standing, concentrating, and problem-solving over extended periods. Having professional documentation of your limitations helps validate your experiences to employers and insurance companies while providing your healthcare team with concrete data to guide treatment decisions and activity recommendations.'
  }
];</parameter>
<parameter name="new_string">    helpText: 'A functional capacity evaluation provides objective documentation of your physical and cognitive abilities, which is crucial for workplace accommodations, disability claims, and treatment planning. This assessment measures your ability to perform specific tasks like lifting, standing, concentrating, and problem-solving over extended periods. Having professional documentation of your limitations helps validate your experiences to employers and insurance companies while providing your healthcare team with concrete data to guide treatment decisions and activity recommendations.'
  },
  {
    id: 'prompt-38',
    prompt: 'Schedule a comprehensive nutrition consultation with a registered dietitian who specializes in chronic illness management and dietary interventions',
    category: 'action',
    helpText: 'Proper nutrition plays a crucial role in managing chronic illness symptoms and can significantly impact inflammation, energy levels, and overall disease progression. A registered dietitian with chronic illness expertise can identify specific nutrients that support your condition, recommend anti-inflammatory foods, and create meal plans that accommodate medication timing and dietary restrictions. They can also help you develop strategies for maintaining adequate nutrition during symptom flares when appetite or digestion may be compromised.'
  }
];</parameter>
</invoke>
